The paper focuses on machine reading and natural language processing, which are core topics in the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to solve the task, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of rule-based and machine-learning baselines, which are common techniques in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The task of interpreting regulations and applying background knowledge also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) concepts.
